# Informatica MCP — Read vs write tools

The Informatica MCP (`informatica` / `user-informatica`) uses env from `mcp.json`, including `INFORMATICA_ALLOW_WRITES`.

## When `INFORMATICA_ALLOW_WRITES` is **false** (default in some setups)

- **Do not call** `informatica_run_mapping_task`, `informatica_stop_job`, or `informatica_run_job` — they will throw unless writes are enabled.
- **Safe tools**: `informatica_session_info`, `informatica_activity_monitor`, `informatica_activity_log`, `informatica_list_tasks`, `informatica_get_mapping_task`.

## When `INFORMATICA_ALLOW_WRITES` is **true**

- Stop/start/run are allowed **only** when the user explicitly asks to run, stop, or restart a job (or has enabled watchlist automation that uses the same APIs).
- The BPEL / service account must still have **Run** and **Stop** privileges in IICS for those tasks; env flag alone does not grant rights.
- Prefer confirming **environment** (e.g. stage vs prod) before mutating jobs.

## External scripts

Watchlist auto-restart and CLI scripts under `informatica-mcp/scripts/` use the same REST API and env vars; they do not go through MCP. Keep credentials in env / `mcp.json`, not in repo files.
